We examined soil carbon storage in 2018 for a salt mangrove-marsh ecotone along the northeastern coast of Florida near St. Augustine. We established (12) 1.5m^2 PVC chamber plots with mangroves of similar size/age and (12) with only salt marsh grasses. Middle site contains an intermediate level of mangroves compared with the other sides.

We examined soil carbon storage in 2018 for a salt marsh-mangrove ecotone along the northeastern coast of Florida near St. Augustine. We established (12) 1.5m^2 PVC chamber plots with mangroves of similar size/age and (12) with only salt marsh grasses. Northern contains the lowest level of mangroves with an average mangrove age around 7.3 years.
